 +---------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                           SECOND QUEST WALKTHROUGH:                         |
 +---------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  +=========================================================================+

  The second quest jumbles the locations of most the levels and items, and adds
  a lot of difficulty to the levels.  In particular, in the levels there are
  now illusionary walls, some that go 2 ways, and some only 1.

  If you follow the walkthrough exactly you'll have an excess on keys, but if
  you explore on your own, try to conserve keys.  It's very helpful to have
  some extra keys.  Never ever buy keys.

  Also there are 3 new monsters, the Red Bubble (takes away your sword,
  PERMANENTLY), the Blue Bubble (gives your sword back), and the Electric Rope.


